OL,3,CBirmingham bin worker redundancies
OL,4,C'likely' as strike negotiations 'over'
OL,6,FBirmingham City Council has announced
OL,7,Fit has reached the "absolute limit" of
OL,8,Fwhat it can offer to resolve a long-
OL,9,Frunning pay dispute with bin workers.
OL,11,FMembers of Unite have been on all-out
OL,12,Fstrike since early March, leading to
OL,13,Frubbish piling up in the streets of
OL,14,Fthe city.
OL,16,FCouncil leader John Cotton said in a
OL,17,Fstatement on Wednesday: "Throughout
OL,18,Fthis process, the council has sought
OL,19,Fto be reasonable and flexible, but we
OL,20,Fhave reached the absolute limit of
OL,21,Fwhat we can offer.
