OL,6,F"So, we will be communicating with our
OL,7,Fstaff and trade unions as to next
OL,8,Fsteps. Voluntary Redundancy remains on
OL,9,Fthe table, as do opportunities for
OL,10,Ftraining and redeployment across the
OL,11,Fcouncil.
OL,13,F"We have worked really hard to end
OL,14,Fthis dispute and we apologise for all
OL,15,Fthe disruption and appreciate
OL,16,Fresidents' patience. This is a service
OL,17,Fthat needs to be improved into one
OL,18,Fthat the residents of Birmingham
OL,19,Fdeserve and I am committed to ensuring
OL,20,Fthat happens."
